    <header>
      <span class="article-category">International Comparisons</span>
      <h1 class="article-title">Most Educated Countries in the World &mdash; The Full Ranking</h1>
      <p class="article-deck">47 countries ranked by tertiary attainment using OECD Education at a Glance 2025. What each top-third nation specifically excels in &mdash; engineers, scientists, teachers, researchers, tradespeople. The paradox where more years of schooling doesn&rsquo;t mean better outcomes. Gender gaps, spending efficiency, and the bottom third.</p>
      <div class="article-meta">
        <span class="meta-pill">Updated March 2026</span>
        <span class="meta-pill">OECD EAG 2025 + 8 datasets</span>
        <span class="meta-pill">~20 min read</span>
        <a href="/methodology" class="meta-pill" style="text-decoration:none;">Methodology &#8594;</a>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="sources-bar">
      <span class="sources-bar-label">Primary sources used</span>
      <div class="source-pills">
        <span class="source-pill">OECD EAG 2025</span>
        <span class="source-pill">UNESCO UIS</span>
        <span class="source-pill">PISA 2022</span>
